ernment announced that its military had defeated the remnants of the LTTE. Since the end of the conflict, the government has enacted an ambitious program of economic development projects, many of which are financed by loans from the Government of China. In addition to efforts to reconstruct its economy, the government has resettled more than 95% of those civilians who were displaced during the final phase of the conflict and released the vast majority of former LTTE combatants captured by Government Security Forces. At the same time, there has been little progress on more contentious and politically difficult issues such as reaching a political settlement with Tamil elected representatives and holding accountable those alleged to have been involved in human rights violations and other abuses during the conflict.','Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka','Colombo',21866445,65610,333.28,'Southern Asia, island in the Indian Ocean, south of India',134500000000,'tropical monsoon; northeast monsoon (December to March); southwest monsoon (June to October)','Sri Lankan rupees (LKR)','LKR');

